                            <comment id="13119821" author="dmlloyd" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 06:54:07 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I think before you give this blocker priority - or even before you file the issue - you should investigate these by hand rather than just relying on an automated tool.  A very quick glance reveals that the ServiceMBeanSupport ones &lt;b&gt;do&lt;/b&gt; in fact have log IDs, they just don&apos;t follow the usual pattern.  The JGroups LogFactory methods are obviously not messages, etc.  The test suite doesn&apos;t need log IDs.  Most - if not all - of these &quot;missing&quot; messages are not missing at all, and this is true for all the projects for which this automated tooling was run, meaning this is just an elaborate time-waster from an engineering perspective.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13120083" author="jamezp" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 11:41:21 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve removed all the log messages that are okay. It looks like there&apos;s only 5 that need to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13120129" author="jamezp" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 12:51:01 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;The EclipseLink message was not converted. I don&apos;t think it needs to be internationalized. It would require some changes too as it&apos;s an extension to EclipseLink logging.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
